---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words With Double N — CINNAMON, PENNANT, ANTENNA & More"
  description="Best double-N words for Scrabble. CINNAMON (12pts), PENNANT (11pts), ANTENNA (7pts). NN pattern strategy for consistent scoring. Free word finder tool."
  keywords="scrabble double n words, cinnamon scrabble, pennant scrabble, antenna scrabble, nn words scrabble, double n strategy, double letter words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words With Double N — CINNAMON, PENNANT, ANTENNA & More",
    "description": "Best double-N words for Scrabble. NN pattern strategy for consistent scoring.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-30",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-n" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best double-N words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "CINNAMON (12pts, 8 letters), PENNANT (11pts, 7 letters), and ANTENNA (7pts). CONNECT and INNOCENT are also strong NN bingo candidates." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How common are NN words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "With 6 N tiles in the bag, NN draws are reasonably common. Over 80 valid NN words exist in SOWPODS, from INN to CINNAMON." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can double-N words help with bingos?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — PENNANT, CHANNEL, CONNECT, INNOCENT are all 7-8 letter NN bingo words. The NN pattern works well with -ING and -ED suffixes." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words With Double N — CINNAMON, PENNANT, ANTENNA & More</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>4 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">With 6 N tiles in the bag, drawing a pair is common. Double-N words combine familiar patterns with solid scoring — especially when they reach bingo length.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CINNAMON</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PENNANT</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ANTENNA</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">N tiles in bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Double-N Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top NN Word</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">CINNAMON — 12 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">C=3, I=1, N=1, N=1, A=1, M=3, O=1, N=1 · 8 letters</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Uses three N tiles. With the bingo bonus, CINNAMON delivers 62 total points from low-value tiles.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏴 PENNANT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · 7 letters · P=3 + NN · Bingo word</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📡 ANTENNA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · 7 letters · All common tiles</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔗 CONNECT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · 7 letters · C=3 pair + NN</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">😇 INNOCENT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · 8 letters · Triple N possible</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">NN Pattern Strategy</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Don't dump N's separately:</span> Two N tiles unlock PENNANT, CHANNEL, CONNECT. Hold the pair when your rack looks promising for bingos.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">NN + suffix combos:</span> RUNNING, PINNING, WINNING all use NN+ING. PLANNED and THINNED use NN+ED. These create bingo-length words from common tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Short NN for tight spots:</span> INN (3pts), ANN (3pts) are useful for parallel plays and filling gaps when longer words won't fit.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CHANNEL</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">STUNNING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ANNOUNCE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RUNNING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Tile Math</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">With <span class="text-white font-medium">6 N tiles</span> in the bag (each worth 1pt), you'll hold NN roughly 1 in 5 games. Memorise the key words — they come up often.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-l/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With Double L</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-words-with-double-letters/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Words With Double Letters</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find double-N words from your tiles — free solver, no sign-up needed</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
